2
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:10,475
is our play painted on the wall

3
00:01:10,475 --> 00:01:12,435
to the left when you enter the building.

4
00:01:13,165 --> 00:01:16,085
The painting originates in the
late 14th century

5
00:01:16,085 --> 00:01:21,975
and the subject was formed by the plague
that visited this landscape.

6
00:01:23,455 --> 00:01:26,800
The artist is
unknown.

7
00:01:27,485 --> 00:01:30,425
I have therefore called the play
Wooden Painting

8
00:01:30,555 --> 00:01:33,565
and follows the painting's story

9
00:01:33,565 --> 00:01:36,875
which starts in the weapon house's
small windows

10
00:01:36,875 --> 00:01:39,675
where the sun shines over a
still-green landscape

11
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:42,875
and ends four meters further in
a dark corner

12
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:47,665
where the final events happen

13
00:01:47,665 --> 00:01:52,405
in a rainy, gray dawn.

14
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:05,375
Nobody may pass further inside

15
00:02:06,795 --> 00:02:09,825
As you can't recognise us,
I forgive you

16
00:02:09,825 --> 00:02:14,245
I can't help it,
but it's forbidden to cross the threshold

17
00:02:14,245 --> 00:02:17,815
And why doesn't your father, brother or
husband tell us that it's forbidden?

18
00:02:18,135 --> 00:02:19,315
My brother's ill.

19
00:02:20,095 --> 00:02:21,935
My father hasn't returned from the war.

20
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:24,615
My husband died three days ago.

21
00:02:26,725 --> 00:02:31,825
I'll have a word with your brother.  He
will recognise both me and my master.

22
00:02:33,385 --> 00:02:35,905
No, don't.
I understand your worry

23
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:39,325
Just because we look dirty and soiled

24
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,285
that doesn't make us villains.

25
00:02:41,655 --> 00:02:42,655
We've got the plague.

26
00:02:42,915 --> 00:02:46,255
Oops, that's not good.
That's disgusting.

27
00:02:47,305 --> 00:02:48,555
Oops.

28
00:02:49,365 --> 00:02:50,515
Nobody escapes.

29
00:02:51,865 --> 00:02:52,865
There's no cure.

30
00:02:53,205 --> 00:02:54,325
No escape.

31
00:02:56,235 --> 00:02:57,965
Do you smell the smoke?

32
00:02:58,505 --> 00:03:01,385
It's been over the woods since this morning.

33
00:03:02,295 --> 00:03:05,335
When you mention it, I do feel something
stinging my nose.

34
00:03:05,675 --> 00:03:08,495
They burned a witch at the crossroads
this morning.

35
00:03:09,315 --> 00:03:12,145
It's considered that she's the cause of
the plague.

36
00:03:12,925 --> 00:03:18,365
By the way, she did admit to having
sexual congress with...  the dark one.

37
00:03:19,635 --> 00:03:22,355
But dear, then everything well and good!

38
00:03:22,355 --> 00:03:25,215
You have to keep up with those damned
witches, whether they conjure up plague...

39
00:03:25,215 --> 00:03:27,195
... or whatever devilish thing they're doing.

40
00:03:28,805 --> 00:03:30,495
My master wants us to continue.

41
00:03:31,495 --> 00:03:32,595
What is your master's name?

42
00:03:33,715 --> 00:03:37,325
His name is Antonius Block, and he's
your master as much as mine.

43
00:03:39,765 --> 00:03:42,785
For ten years we sat down in the holy
land, letting snakes bite us...

44
00:03:42,785 --> 00:03:45,855
... animals gnaw at us, heathens light
us on fire...

45
00:03:45,855 --> 00:03:48,885
... wine poison us, women giving us lice...

46
00:03:48,885 --> 00:03:52,075
... fleas eat is up, and fevers burn us up.

47
00:03:52,245 --> 00:03:53,445
For God's honour!

48
00:04:02,215 --> 00:04:04,715
Now you're throwing twigs at me, my lord...

49
00:04:04,715 --> 00:04:10,725
... but I was right.  Our crusade was so
stupid that only an idealist could have
thought of it.

50
00:04:11,345 --> 00:04:14,325
Just look at my master.  He can't talk.

51
00:04:14,855 --> 00:04:19,635
The dirty heathens captured him one
Sunday morning during services.

52
00:04:19,715 --> 00:04:22,115
And they cut his tongue out of his mouth.

53
00:04:22,675 --> 00:04:39,715
Thanks to me...
... the plague...

54
00:04:40,085 --> 00:04:46,225
... more insulting than what we've experienced.

55
00:04:47,295 --> 00:04:49,325
I don't give a damn about the plague.

56
00:04:50,895 --> 00:04:52,795
Goodbye, my girl.

57
00:04:52,795 --> 00:04:55,405
Even if I lack funds for your information

58
00:04:55,405 --> 00:04:57,795
you'll have to keep an account until we
meet in heaven.

59
00:04:58,395 --> 00:04:59,675
If you get there, that is.

60
00:05:14,505 --> 00:05:15,595
They should obey.

61
00:05:15,915 --> 00:05:16,915


62
00:05:17,185 --> 00:05:19,155


63
00:05:19,815 --> 00:05:22,455
They haven't seen their infected eyes,
their hands

64
00:05:22,455 --> 00:05:25,175
the blood that foams around their eyes
and mouths.

65
00:05:26,055 --> 00:05:29,315
They haven't seen the boils on their necks.

66
00:05:29,805 --> 00:05:33,485
Every morning it's bigger than in the
evening.

67
00:05:33,575 --> 00:05:36,285
And water and pus runs from it.

68
00:05:36,285 --> 00:05:40,925
On some it grows as big as a
child's head, and their bodies...

69
00:05:40,925 --> 00:05:43,935
... and their bodies shrink so their
limbs become ropes of madness.

70
00:05:44,445 --> 00:05:46,375
They try to tear the boils off.

71
00:05:46,375 --> 00:05:48,195
They bit their hands.

72
00:05:48,195 --> 00:05:50,495
They tear their veins open with their
nails.

73
00:05:50,495 --> 00:05:52,855
Their screams tear the clouds.

74
00:05:53,455 --> 00:05:56,665
Then they dance over the floor.

75
00:05:56,665 --> 00:05:59,795
Then they fall, and then they gasp

76
00:06:01,815 --> 00:06:03,065
And then they die.

77
00:06:03,895 --> 00:06:05,015
In the trenches.

78
00:06:05,755 --> 00:06:06,995
In the barns.

79
00:06:07,525 --> 00:06:08,665
On the farms.

80
00:06:09,085 --> 00:06:10,135
In the river.

81
00:06:10,805 --> 00:06:12,975
In the stoves.

82
00:06:12,975 --> 00:06:15,975
The people flee the cities.

83
00:06:15,975 --> 00:06:18,325
They go north

84
00:06:18,325 --> 00:06:21,385
and the entire time a shadow follows them.

85
00:06:21,385 --> 00:06:22,545
A stricter master.

86
00:06:23,665 --> 00:06:25,405
New areas are hit.

87
00:06:26,605 --> 00:06:27,805
It's the end times.

88
00:06:28,285 --> 00:06:30,975
In the sunset it's as if you can see the
horsemen.

89
00:06:30,975 --> 00:06:32,985
The wild riders of the apocalypse.

90
00:06:43,645 --> 00:06:44,645
Poor little Jens.

91
00:06:47,085 --> 00:06:48,445
How dark the forest is.

92
00:06:49,595 --> 00:06:51,255
Even if the sun has barely set.

93
00:06:55,225 --> 00:06:58,395
A huge crab sits under my ribs and grabs
at my heart.

94
00:07:01,155 --> 00:07:02,745
Perhaps I should try singing a little song.

95
00:07:06,285 --> 00:07:10,465
In the ocean the fishes swim

96
00:07:10,465 --> 00:07:13,035
Big ships are rocked.

97
00:07:13,035 --> 00:07:15,985
Sensible people die like flies.

98
00:07:18,985 --> 00:07:20,635
Are you afraid, Jens?

99
00:07:22,905 --> 00:07:23,905
Uh-uh.

100
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:28,505
Are you afraid, little Jens?

101
00:07:30,165 --> 00:07:31,285
No...

102
00:07:33,765 --> 00:07:37,175
Aren't you at all afraid, my poor little
Jens?

103
00:07:41,465 --> 00:07:45,665
Yes!

104
00:07:47,255 --> 00:07:49,115
I am so scared that an accident could
happen at any time.

105
00:07:49,275 --> 00:07:52,655
But my stomach is as empty as infinity.

106
00:07:55,325 --> 00:07:57,155
But who are you, my beautiful girl?

107
00:07:58,105 --> 00:07:59,315
Aren't you afraid of the dark?

108
00:08:01,725 --> 00:08:03,295
Can I join you?

109
00:08:04,125 --> 00:08:07,145
My master and I are just resting.

110
00:08:07,145 --> 00:08:10,075
You see, we've just strolled from the
holy country.

111
00:08:10,075 --> 00:08:13,515
- So we're a bit tired, you see.
- OK, then I'll... rest, too.

112
00:08:13,815 --> 00:08:16,545
Follow me into the bushes over there.

113
00:08:16,545 --> 00:08:17,765
Why should I do that?

114
00:08:21,075 --> 00:08:25,095
Perhaps we could pick some blueberries,
for instance?

115
00:08:27,325 --> 00:08:30,575
- It's been so long.
- If you knew who I am...

116
00:08:31,105 --> 00:08:33,955
... you wouldn't suggest picking
blueberries.

117
00:08:33,955 --> 00:08:36,535
Or anything else, for that matter.

118
00:08:36,535 --> 00:08:39,195
- Who are you then, if I may ask?
- I'm the witch!

119
00:08:39,485 --> 00:08:42,165
That they burned over at the crossroads
this morning.

120
00:08:43,825 --> 00:08:46,875
Then you really shouldn't be standing
here, being dead and all.

121
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:48,125
Of course I'm dead!

122
00:08:49,345 --> 00:08:50,575
Oh!  Then you're a ghost?

123
00:08:51,425 --> 00:08:54,585
And I don't believe in ghosts, which
means that you don't exist.

124
00:08:54,585 --> 00:08:57,645
Which means that you can't be standing
there bothering me.

125
00:08:57,645 --> 00:09:00,695
Unless we're dead too, and transformed
into ghosts.  If that's the case,

126
00:09:00,695 --> 00:09:03,715
then I don't give a damn, so don't say
another word until the end of days.

127
00:09:04,065 --> 00:09:07,045
Perhaps you and your master participated
in the execution?

128
00:09:07,045 --> 00:09:08,475
No, unfortunately!  We've just been abroad.

129
00:09:10,745 --> 00:09:13,885
Near the morning, I fell asleep for a
while.

130
00:09:14,665 --> 00:09:20,105
But I awoke almost immediately by the
crowd hissing outside the prison.  I was
afraid, and I cried.

131
00:09:21,355 --> 00:09:25,375
But that didn't help.  Everything had
already been decided.

132
00:09:26,515 --> 00:09:29,055
I climbed up to the little window and
looked down on the yard.

133
00:09:31,645 --> 00:09:35,205
The wagon they were going to drive me
away in was there.

134
00:09:36,405 --> 00:09:38,055
The priest had also arrived.

135
00:09:38,735 --> 00:09:42,285
But I couldn't see whether the
executioner was there.

136
00:09:45,175 --> 00:09:46,605
The sun was rising.

137
00:09:48,195 --> 00:09:50,305
There wasn't a cloud in the skies.

138
00:09:51,765 --> 00:09:53,355
It was completely empty.

139
00:09:56,495 --> 00:09:58,495
I stood there, looking at the people.

140
00:09:59,485 --> 00:10:01,775
And I was able to distinguish their
faces.

141
00:10:02,995 --> 00:10:05,685
And their voices entered my ears.

142
00:10:06,245 --> 00:10:08,275
And they were like evil birds.

143
00:10:11,165 --> 00:10:15,425
And then I looked at my hands, holding
on to the protrusion on the wall.

144
00:10:15,425 --> 00:10:19,395
The nails were black with blood, and
broken.

145
00:10:19,425 --> 00:10:24,065
But my knuckles whitened, and all my
strength remained!

146
00:10:26,195 --> 00:10:28,055
Then voices could be heard in the hall.

147
00:10:28,765 --> 00:10:31,685
The door was opened, and I fell down
from the wall.

148
00:10:32,585 --> 00:10:36,775
I lay with my forehead on the rough
planks that stank of rotten straw.

149
00:10:39,025 --> 00:10:43,685
They bent down, took me across the
waist, and they pulled my shoulders

150
00:10:43,785 --> 00:10:47,645
and they placed an iron claw over
my neck.

151
00:10:48,365 --> 00:10:49,755
And I was cold.

152
00:10:50,665 --> 00:10:52,875
So cold I couldn't speak.

153
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:54,975
Couldn't scream.

154
00:10:56,175 --> 00:10:57,675
Couldn't walk.

155
00:10:58,995 --> 00:11:00,835
But they pulled on my collar.

156
00:11:01,275 --> 00:11:09,515
They pulled me down the stone steps and
through a long hall, and every time I
fell, I almost choked.

157
00:11:10,185 --> 00:11:11,925
Then they pulled on the chain.

158
00:11:14,485 --> 00:11:17,565
But they didn't touch my body.

159
00:11:18,725 --> 00:11:19,875
Like the other guards.

160
00:11:21,335 --> 00:11:24,455
They didn't laugh and make fun of me

161
00:11:24,455 --> 00:11:27,135
like those who cut my hair.  No, they
were silent and worried.

162
00:11:27,685 --> 00:11:30,245
They pulled my collar and they were
afraid.

163
00:11:32,715 --> 00:11:39,175
Because they knew that He accompanied me
and hold onto my dress.

164
00:11:39,655 --> 00:11:42,315
Then the doors opened and the sun struck
my face.

165
00:11:42,595 --> 00:11:44,345
And there was like an outcry in the sun.

166
00:11:45,135 --> 00:11:47,325
And the morning wind tore up sand

167
00:11:47,495 --> 00:11:49,025
and threw it in our faces.

168
00:11:53,055 --> 00:11:54,705
I sat in the wagon.

169
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:56,195
Back to front.

170
00:11:57,705 --> 00:12:01,775
Tethered, so that I had to hold my head
safely against my chest.

171
00:12:02,815 --> 00:12:06,315
And when the wagon shook along the road,
it hurt.

172
00:12:06,935 --> 00:12:10,205
Because the iron cut into my throat.
But I didn't scream.

173
00:12:12,775 --> 00:12:14,605
The pain helped me.

174
00:12:16,385 --> 00:12:19,655
The rocks on the road helped me.

175
00:12:20,825 --> 00:12:26,825
The creaking wheels helped me.

176
00:12:26,825 --> 00:12:29,915
There was nothing in front and nothing
behind me.

177
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:35,355
And the sun burned in red waves through
my eyelids

178
00:12:35,355 --> 00:12:36,755
and I heard the stamping of hundreds of
feet.

179
00:12:40,255 --> 00:12:42,425
The road dust rose like smoke.

180
00:12:45,175 --> 00:12:50,315
I felt how the people around me
breathed, and how their pulses beat.

181
00:12:50,915 --> 00:12:53,075
And their eyes widened.

182
00:12:54,055 --> 00:12:55,055
But they were all silent.

183
00:12:58,645 --> 00:13:01,175
When we reached the place by
the crossroads

184
00:13:01,485 --> 00:13:03,485
they loosened my tether.

185
00:13:04,315 --> 00:13:05,845
And I bent my head backwards.

186
00:13:10,645 --> 00:13:12,255
Over the pines

187
00:13:13,525 --> 00:13:15,685
above everything

188
00:13:16,475 --> 00:13:19,255
there were streams of thin clouds.

189
00:13:20,105 --> 00:13:21,605
Like hands.

190
00:13:23,885 --> 00:13:25,145
Then I smelled the smoke!

191
00:13:26,615 --> 00:13:29,635
It was coming from a huge heap of
twigs and everybody started coughing.

192
00:13:29,685 --> 00:13:30,685
The flames rose.  It was a huge fire.

193
00:13:30,905 --> 00:13:32,485
It heated our faces

194
00:13:33,005 --> 00:13:35,005
and I turned away.

195
00:13:37,905 --> 00:13:43,565
And behind me, He stood.

196
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:48,555
And his mouth curved upwards.

197
00:13:49,355 --> 00:13:52,505
And his eyes became round and clear.

198
00:13:54,515 --> 00:13:56,395
He came close to me.

199
00:13:59,115 --> 00:14:03,225
I felt his breath against my cheek.

200
00:14:03,595 --> 00:14:06,305
And He put His hand on my thigh.

201
00:14:11,155 --> 00:14:13,965
I turned towards the heap.

202
00:14:14,085 --> 00:14:16,735
And all the people who were hiding
behind it.

203
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:20,565
I stretched my fingers out.  I stood on
my toes.

204
00:14:20,675 --> 00:14:23,805
I stretched as far as I could.

205
00:14:23,805 --> 00:14:26,395
And then I laughed!  I laughed...

206
00:14:29,695 --> 00:14:32,515
But it sounds like when a small
child laughs.

207
00:14:32,515 --> 00:14:34,235
So I started screaming.

208
00:14:34,595 --> 00:14:36,985
Words appeared in my scream.

209
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:39,395
They were like fishes in a lake.

210
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:43,055
Now the wheel is turning.  Now the sand
is raging.

211
00:14:43,475 --> 00:14:45,805
Now the night bird is screaming.

212
00:14:45,805 --> 00:14:48,565
Now everything collides.

213
00:14:49,525 --> 00:14:50,525
The viper.

214
00:14:51,565 --> 00:14:52,875
Now the wheel has stopped.

215
00:14:54,075 --> 00:14:57,055
Now the holy rites are rising.

216
00:15:02,415 --> 00:15:03,905
Now the wheel stands still.

217
00:15:05,665 --> 00:15:06,895
Now there's silence.

218
00:15:07,605 --> 00:15:09,745
Now the leap is close.

219
00:15:10,675 --> 00:15:13,625
Now the sand has its own.

220
00:15:15,485 --> 00:15:18,105
Now the mountains are roaring.

221
00:15:19,555 --> 00:15:23,195
Now the river is gaping.

222
00:15:24,445 --> 00:15:25,765
Now they're here.

223
00:15:34,085 --> 00:15:37,715
Then they struck me across the mouth
with a cane so I fell down.

224
00:15:40,595 --> 00:15:42,485
Then they tied me to a ladder.

225
00:15:43,555 --> 00:15:45,445
And put it into the fire.

226
00:15:46,215 --> 00:15:48,955
And the flames flew up.

227
00:15:49,295 --> 00:15:50,945
Enveloped my clothes.

228
00:15:51,415 --> 00:15:55,245
And before I fell into the pyre with my
face first

229
00:15:56,265 --> 00:15:58,695
I burned like a torch.

230
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:03,805
They sang a psalm.

231
00:16:07,405 --> 00:16:10,245
But I was no longer scared.

232
00:16:12,945 --> 00:16:17,405
He held his furry body in front of
mine.

233
00:16:18,035 --> 00:16:19,585
And we fell

234
00:16:20,435 --> 00:16:22,815
into a deep lake.

235
00:16:24,965 --> 00:16:28,405
He enveloped me

236
00:16:29,555 --> 00:16:32,755
and I wasn't cold any more.

237
00:16:46,965 --> 00:16:48,325
Sorry for disturbing.

238
00:16:48,945 --> 00:16:51,815
Have any of you seen my wife?

239
00:16:52,475 --> 00:16:55,275
No, we haven't seen even a cat.

240
00:16:55,545 --> 00:16:56,545
That's too bad.

241
00:16:57,215 --> 00:16:58,545
Has she disappeared?

242
00:17:00,905 --> 00:17:02,045
She'd gone off with a jester.

243
00:17:03,465 --> 00:17:06,335
If she's got that bad taste, I think you
should just let her run off.

244
00:17:06,335 --> 00:17:08,825
Don't do her the honour of running
around the woods looking for her.

245
00:17:09,265 --> 00:17:10,335
That's not it, my lord.

246
00:17:10,675 --> 00:17:13,135
I had rather thought I was going to kill
her.

247
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:17,185
Oh, I see.  Well, that's a different
thing altogether.

248
00:17:17,185 --> 00:17:19,585
I'm going to kill the cheating jester,
too.

249
00:17:20,325 --> 00:17:25,545
There's too many of those, anyway.  Even
if they haven't done anything, they
should be killed.

250
00:17:26,285 --> 00:17:32,275
You see, my wife has always been so
interested in...  the art of theatre.

251
00:17:32,865 --> 00:17:34,575
And that was her misfortune.

252
00:17:35,265 --> 00:17:37,825
Her misfortune, but not mine.

253
00:17:37,825 --> 00:17:40,315
Because one that's born as a mistake
can't be affected by misfortune.

254
00:17:40,885 --> 00:17:43,895
Of what kind is self-evident.

255
00:17:53,685 --> 00:17:55,305
Are you married, by any chance?

