00:34:59,235 --> 00:35:03,225
Maria is a bit outside the group with
her child.

502
00:35:03,955 --> 00:35:07,695
She looks at the moonlight which is no
longer silent and dead.

503
00:35:08,115 --> 00:35:10,995
It's secretive and shifting.

504
00:35:14,625 --> 00:35:19,545
One morning, the holy virgin went to the
well to get water.

505
00:35:21,695 --> 00:35:27,955
The lizards scurried across the stones,
and one was in the light and one was in
the shade.

506
00:35:29,755 --> 00:35:34,705
She leaned against the well and
peered down into the dark water.

507
00:35:36,135 --> 00:35:37,945
Her cheeks had gotten thinner.

508
00:35:38,705 --> 00:35:41,395
And her eyes had grown bigger.

509
00:35:43,215 --> 00:35:47,675
It felt heavy carrying the child just
that morning in the white heat of
the sun.

510
00:35:48,035 --> 00:35:53,105
So she cried a bit, and he tears dropped
down into the well's water.

511
00:35:54,925 --> 00:35:56,605
And when she'd finished crying

512
00:35:57,075 --> 00:35:58,605
and that didn't take long

513
00:35:59,165 --> 00:36:02,545
she felt a bit better, almost happy

514
00:36:03,085 --> 00:36:04,965
and she took some water in her cup.

515
00:36:06,525 --> 00:36:09,685
The sun sparkled in the tall pines

516
00:36:09,725 --> 00:36:14,075
and the light splashed all over her red
dress and her naked feet.

517
00:36:15,295 --> 00:36:18,475
She wiped her tears, salt stinging
her cheeks.

518
00:36:18,475 --> 00:36:20,805
She drank from the fresh water.

519
00:36:21,125 --> 00:36:24,765
She drank from her hands that she formed
into a cup.

520
00:36:27,525 --> 00:36:28,525
Then...

521
00:36:29,905 --> 00:36:33,205
The child moved in her womb.

522
00:36:34,795 --> 00:36:38,115
And she laughed loudly in
her loneliness.

523
00:36:39,695 --> 00:36:44,005
She straightened her back, with
arms akimbo.

524
00:36:44,585 --> 00:36:48,795
She raised the water vessel in her
brown, sinewy arms.

525
00:36:50,325 --> 00:36:54,925
The she walked the few steps up to the
carpenter's house

526
00:36:54,925 --> 00:36:57,385
She walked through the sweltering heat
of the morning

527
00:36:57,455 --> 00:37:01,145
but her steps were almost like a dance.

528
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:09,165
From the roads you could hear the
barking of the sheepdogs and the shouts
from the shepherds.

529
00:37:09,855 --> 00:37:12,625
They were driving their herds to
the mountains

530
00:37:12,785 --> 00:37:15,905
to the olive groves' refreshing shadow.

531
00:37:20,245 --> 00:37:25,685
This was my song about the virgin Mary.

532
00:37:29,555 --> 00:37:32,455
We have reached the starting point.

533
00:37:33,125 --> 00:37:34,865
By the border stone.

534
00:37:35,925 --> 00:37:41,005
You have walked in a circle and now
you're sitting, waiting and freezing in
the dawn.

535
00:37:42,495 --> 00:37:47,375
The wind is increasing and the clouds
are amassing at the horizon which is
greying in the dawn.

536
00:37:47,375 --> 00:37:50,035


537
00:37:53,835 --> 00:37:54,875
Who is the woman standing over there?

538
00:37:57,745 --> 00:37:59,865
The wife of the knight Antonius Block.

539
00:38:00,955 --> 00:38:03,915
I left the farm because of the plague.

540
00:38:04,925 --> 00:38:06,485
I was one of the last ones.

541
00:38:07,285 --> 00:38:08,315
What are you doing here?

542
00:38:09,865 --> 00:38:11,665
Do you see the fires over there?

543
00:38:12,675 --> 00:38:13,835
Do you hear the music?

544
00:38:15,065 --> 00:38:21,845
It's the other country's soldiers who
have blocked the border with a tall
fence that crosses the entire country
from coast to coast.

545
00:38:22,895 --> 00:38:24,565
There's soldiers everywhere.

546
00:38:25,135 --> 00:38:28,355
Nobody from the plague-stricken country
are allowed entrance.

547
00:38:29,525 --> 00:38:31,325
We just have to wait.

548
00:38:32,455 --> 00:38:33,975
What are we waiting for?

549
00:38:34,635 --> 00:38:35,645
For nothing.

550
00:38:36,715 --> 00:38:37,875
For the plague.

551
00:38:49,945 --> 00:38:51,965
Poor Atonius Block.

552
00:38:52,665 --> 00:38:54,505
Poor dear; do you recognise me?

553
00:38:55,625 --> 00:38:57,535
I can see that it's you now.

554
00:38:58,635 --> 00:39:01,655
Somewhere in your eyes, somewhere in
your face

555
00:39:01,655 --> 00:39:06,385
but hidden away, but scared, is that boy
who left all those years ago.

556
00:39:07,685 --> 00:39:10,045
Was is a good and amusing crusade?

557
00:39:10,875 --> 00:39:12,595
Did you manage to kill a lot
of heathens?

558
00:39:13,555 --> 00:39:17,475
Did you ride really fast and smash a lot
of swords and lances?

559
00:39:18,385 --> 00:39:21,165
Did you pray a lot of prayers at the
holy grave?

560
00:39:21,615 --> 00:39:23,695
Did you rape a lot of women?

561
00:39:30,545 --> 00:39:31,545
Are you cold?

562
00:39:32,965 --> 00:39:34,195
Do you want to borrow my shawl?

563
00:39:35,295 --> 00:39:36,295
No?

564
00:39:36,535 --> 00:39:39,385
In the ocean fishes swim

565
00:39:39,475 --> 00:39:42,165
Big ships are rocked

566
00:39:44,295 --> 00:39:45,295
Silence!

567
00:39:46,605 --> 00:39:47,605
Don't you hear that?

568
00:39:48,895 --> 00:39:50,125
What are we supposed to hear?

569
00:39:51,675 --> 00:39:54,365
Now the roosters in the other country
are crowing where the dawn is meeting
the plain.

570
00:39:55,805 --> 00:39:57,475
Now the fires are going out.

571
00:39:58,815 --> 00:40:00,425
Now the wind is calming down.

572
00:40:02,775 --> 00:40:05,825
Now the rain is starting to fall, silent
and mild.

573
00:40:09,175 --> 00:40:16,165
Now we're standing here, tightly
together, waiting for somebody that's
coming towards us from over there.

574
00:40:31,465 --> 00:40:33,145
It's a powerful man.

575
00:40:33,945 --> 00:40:34,945
A knight.

576
00:40:36,865 --> 00:40:37,865
A gentleman.

577
00:40:39,065 --> 00:40:41,455
And he's got a young girl in his
entourage.

578
00:40:41,835 --> 00:40:45,085
And a jester with his lute on his back.

579
00:40:47,025 --> 00:40:48,025
There's coming here.

580
00:40:49,525 --> 00:40:53,665
They're coming here, to us, through
the silent dawn rain.

581
00:41:10,625 --> 00:41:11,625
Good morning, my high lord.

582
00:41:13,745 --> 00:41:16,085
We're standing here, together, waiting
for you.

583
00:41:18,665 --> 00:41:20,255
My name is Jens.

584
00:41:22,515 --> 00:41:24,375
A Jens person.

585
00:41:24,825 --> 00:41:28,495
Who talks a lot during an
endless stroll.

586
00:41:31,355 --> 00:41:34,165
There's a scrawny and miserable knight.

587
00:41:34,735 --> 00:41:44,445
With a whole lot of confused and
feverish thoughts under his hat.

588
00:41:47,915 --> 00:41:49,655
I'm the knight's wife.

589
00:41:54,825 --> 00:41:57,515
There's a little witch, who, from what
I've heard

590
00:41:57,515 --> 00:41:59,895
is supposed to have pleasured herself
with the dark one.

591
00:42:00,915 --> 00:42:02,705
She was burned for her faith.

592
00:42:03,205 --> 00:42:06,105
By now she's probably
pretty disappointed.

593
00:42:14,075 --> 00:42:15,275
I'm a smith by profession.

594
00:42:16,005 --> 00:42:17,035
And pretty good.

595
00:42:22,565 --> 00:42:24,105
This is my wife, Lisa.

596
00:42:25,135 --> 00:42:27,275
Curtsy for the lord, Lisa.

597
00:42:29,905 --> 00:42:32,325
She's hard to handle, sometimes.

598
00:42:33,135 --> 00:42:35,955
We've had some hullabaloo, so to say.

599
00:42:36,965 --> 00:42:39,345
A bit more than most people.

600
00:42:39,825 --> 00:42:42,265
It was the jester's fault.

601
00:42:42,775 --> 00:42:44,485
Ask him yourself; he's standing
right there.

602
00:42:49,175 --> 00:42:52,405
Over there's a woman who calls
herself Maria.

603
00:42:52,715 --> 00:42:55,905
She's been running days and nights
to escape.

604
00:42:56,985 --> 00:43:00,105
Perhaps not so much for her own sake, as
for the child's.

605
00:43:01,525 --> 00:43:03,315
Now she stands there, quiet, and waits.

606
00:43:12,395 --> 00:43:15,365
I can tell you what the knight is
shouting, even if his tongue has been
stolen from him

607
00:43:15,365 --> 00:43:20,225
and only strange sounds escape him.

608
00:43:21,155 --> 00:43:26,015
Every morning he stretches his arms
towards the saints, towards god.

609
00:43:26,435 --> 00:43:30,385
Often he shouts in their holy ears for
them to hear him.

610
00:43:31,295 --> 00:43:34,795
Time and time again, he's shook by
certainty.

611
00:43:35,315 --> 00:43:40,835
Through fogs of spiritual lethargy he's
struck by god's presence

612
00:43:40,835 --> 00:43:42,855
like a blow from a huge bell.

613
00:43:44,135 --> 00:43:47,085
Suddenly his emptiness is filled with
a music

614
00:43:47,085 --> 00:43:51,515
without notes, but carried as if
by voices

615
00:43:52,895 --> 00:43:56,895
Then he shouts through all his
darknesses, and his shout is like
a whisper.

616
00:43:58,125 --> 00:43:59,125
To your presence, o god.

617
00:43:59,875 --> 00:44:01,895
For your honour, I live.

618
00:44:02,425 --> 00:44:03,425
For your honour.

619
00:44:04,925 --> 00:44:06,255
That's what he's shouting in
the darkness.

620
00:44:08,095 --> 00:44:16,265
Then the terrible thing happens: His
certainty goes out, as if somebody blew
out a candle.

621
00:44:16,765 --> 00:44:18,705
The huge bell falls silent.

622
00:44:20,015 --> 00:44:21,425
The darkness pulses even darker.

623
00:44:21,975 --> 00:44:25,695
It forces itself through his throat and
presses against his mouth.

624
00:44:27,385 --> 00:44:30,325
The curses appear through his stomach,
his hair, his eyes.

625
00:44:30,375 --> 00:44:31,875
Like a predator

626
00:44:32,285 --> 00:44:35,245
like shine small snakes

627
00:44:35,685 --> 00:44:38,125
like evil little birds with
hoarse screams

628
00:44:39,115 --> 00:44:41,715
Then his darkness is spotted by blood

629
00:44:42,105 --> 00:44:45,185
Then his wounds expand.

630
00:44:48,635 --> 00:44:52,595
With all respect for the strict lord, I
ask you to stop making those sounds.

631
00:44:53,275 --> 00:44:56,125
Out there in the darkness, that you
claim to visit

632
00:44:56,125 --> 00:44:59,455
where presumably we all visit like
stupid little heavenly bodies

633
00:44:59,455 --> 00:45:04,165
in that darkness you won't find anybody
to care about your complaints or
your suffering.

634
00:45:04,495 --> 00:45:07,935
So dry your tears and reflect in
your indifference.

635
00:45:08,375 --> 00:45:09,895
From me you could have gotten a herb.

636
00:45:10,365 --> 00:45:12,965
To laxatively purge your problems
with eternity.

637
00:45:14,465 --> 00:45:16,235
It seems to be too late now.

638
00:45:17,185 --> 00:45:20,155
Feel, at least, in these final minutes,
the incommensurate triumph

639
00:45:20,155 --> 00:45:23,385
to be able to roll your eyes and move
your toes.

640
00:45:23,385 --> 00:45:24,385
Be silent.

641
00:45:26,925 --> 00:45:27,925
I'll be quiet.

642
00:45:28,555 --> 00:45:30,065
But under protest.

643
00:45:31,325 --> 00:45:33,525
I got a bit embarrassed, I admit that.

644
00:45:33,975 --> 00:45:37,535
But should I just give up without free
will and resistance?

645
00:45:39,655 --> 00:45:44,505
With all due respect for the
strict lord.

646
00:45:44,965 --> 00:45:45,965
Quiet.

647
00:45:47,445 --> 00:45:49,405
The jester is tuning his lute.

648
00:45:50,035 --> 00:45:52,635
The strict lord is inviting us to dance.

649
00:46:04,615 --> 00:46:06,675
He wants us to hold hands.

650
00:46:07,555 --> 00:46:10,375
And then thread the dance in a long row.

651
00:46:11,645 --> 00:46:13,915
First the strict lord.

652
00:46:14,995 --> 00:46:17,035
The musician brings up the rear.

653
00:46:18,785 --> 00:46:21,855
Away from the dawn we're going.

654
00:46:22,875 --> 00:46:25,635
Away towards the dark country

655
00:46:25,635 --> 00:46:28,045
while the rain is washing down
our faces.

656
00:46:30,445 --> 00:46:32,925
Come to the dance, my children,
my friends.

657
00:46:33,945 --> 00:46:36,315
The strict lord is impatient.

658
00:46:37,035 --> 00:46:38,995
And the music has just...

659
00:47:17,915 --> 00:47:18,915

